{"meta":{"domain":"subjects","kid":"5143","authors":[{"fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre","id":"6"}],"title":"","dates":{"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:27 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:27 UTC"}},"nodes":[{"index":0,"parent_index":-1,"body":"<p class=\"Paragraph\">In affective constructions, the subject is in the absolutive and the object in the dative. The construction is governed mainly by verbs of feeling such as <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f51\u0f42\u0f60\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cto like,\u201d <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f5e\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cto be afraid,\u201d <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f5a\u0f72\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f5f\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cto get angry,\u201d <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f67\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f66\u0f0b<\/span> \u201cto be amazed,\u201d etc.<\/p><p><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f5a\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f72\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f9f\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f5e\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0d<\/span> \u201cTsering was afraid of the horse.\u201d<\/p>","title":""}]}